# Generated retrieval embeddings (regenerate via `cd CausalSmith/tools && npm run embed:library`).
# The meta sidecars (library_embeddings[.<view>].meta.json) ARE committed for staleness checks;
# the large float32 matrices are not. Views: nl (default), nbr (neighbourhood — enabled),
# stmt (statement — off by default, so its meta is local too).
library_embeddings*.f32
library_embeddings.stmt.meta.json

# Fine-tuned retrieval encoder (1.3GB; regenerate via scripts/train_biencoder.py)
retrieval_model_ft/

# Fine-tuned cross-encoder reranker (Phase 2c; 1.1GB; regenerate via scripts/train_reranker.py).
# The meta sidecar (retrieval_reranker.meta.json) IS committed so the query side knows the
# passage view + base; the weights are not.
retrieval_reranker_ft/
